Package: mismeasured
Type: Package
Title: Bias Correction for GLMs with Measurement Error and Misclassification
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maciej", "Beresewicz", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "maciej.beresewicz@ue.poznan.pl",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8281-4301")),
    person("Michal", "Warmuz", role = "aut"))
Description: Correction methods for generalized linear models with measurement error
    and misclassification. Provides two main interfaces: 'simex()' for
    Simulation-Extrapolation (SIMEX) and MC-SIMEX with a formula interface using
    'me()' and 'mc()' terms, and 'mcglm()' for analytical bias-correction methods
    (BCA, BCM, corrected score) and one-step joint mixture-likelihood estimation
    following Battaglia, Christensen, Hansen and Sacher (2025,
    <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2402.15585>). Supports binary and multicategory misclassified
    covariates, Poisson, Binomial, and Gaussian families, as well as multinomial
    response models. The simulation step uses compiled C++ code via 'Rcpp' and
    'RcppEigen' for fast IRLS fitting. Implements both the standard MC-SIMEX
    (Kuechenhoff et al., 2006, <doi:10.1111/j.1541-0420.2005.00396.x>) and the
    improved exact-correction method (Sevilimedu and Yu, 2026,
    <doi:10.1002/sim.70418>). Based on Cook and Stefanski (1994)
    <doi:10.1080/01621459.1994.10476871>.
